Sec. 20-94. - Fair or good condition trees. 
A tree in fair or good condition must meet the following minimum standards: 
(1)	An estimated life expectancy of greater than ten years.
(2)	A relatively sound and solid trunk with only minor decay and small cavities that comprise an area of depth of less than 33 percent of the adjacent diameter of the tree. 
(3)	No more than 25 percent of the base of the trunk or primary structural roots should exhibit dieback. 
(4)	No major insect or pathological problem.
(5)	No more than 33 percent of the tree's canopy can be missing limbs or be comprised of major dead limbs. 
(Ord. of 1-13-2010, app. C)

